These are good points, but I view their efforts on ARC more as them expanding the Chrome store&#x27;s app catalog than Chrome OS completely eating Android.<p>And as an aside, I think many developers simply don&#x27;t devote the effort to fully developing their Android apps for Chrome OS. I have an (albeit simple) Android app I publish on Chrome OS, and it&#x27;s my product&#x27;s most popular platform. So it gets special attention, and supports resizing with the fairly undocumented &quot;resize&quot; value in the app&#x27;s manifest:<p><pre><code>    &quot;arc_metadata&quot;: {
      &quot;resize&quot;: &quot;reconfigure&quot;,
      &quot;formFactor&quot;: &quot;tablet&quot;,
      &quot;orientation&quot;: &quot;landscape&quot;,
    }</code></pre>
